text: Boone County is a county in the U.S. state of Kentucky. As of the 2020 census, the population was 135,968, making it the fourth-most populous county in Kentucky. Its county seat is Burlington. The county was formed in 1798 and was named for frontiersman Daniel Boone. == References == Category:1798 establishments in Kentucky Category:Kentucky counties
title: Boone County, Kentucky
